GROUP BY -: GROUP BY is a SQL clause used to aggregate rows that share the same values in specified columns into summary rows.
======================= OR ========================
One-line definition:
"Put similar things together, then calculate something about each group"

Basic idea: Instead of returning every individual row, GROUP BY collapses rows with matching values into a single row per group — usually 
so you can apply aggregate functions like COUNT, SUM, AVG, MIN, or MAX.

Syntax -:
SELECT column, AGGREGATE_FUNCTION(other_column)
FROM table
GROUP BY column;


'''''''''
SELECT column_name, AGGREGATE_FUNCTION(column_name)
FROM table_name
WHERE condition
GROUP BY column_name
HAVING condition
ORDER BY column_name;
```Order of Clauses

Always follow this order 
```
SELECT
FROM
WHERE
GROUP BY
HAVING
ORDER BY
